{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Question",
  "name": "Does Webflow support GitHub-connected deployments and modern frameworks like Next.js?",
  "acceptedAnswer": {
    "@type": "Answer",
    "text": "Yes, Webflow Cloud provides a serverless hosting and deployment platform that seamlessly integrates with GitHub, enabling developers to deploy full-stack web applications using modern frameworks like Next.js and Astro directly to Webflow sites. This integration eliminates the need for separate hosting services or complex DNS configuration, allowing teams to maintain their existing development workflows while leveraging Webflow&#39;s visual development capabilities. Webflow’s platform supports multiple deployment environments (production, staging, development) and works in conjunction with DevLink to ensure consistent design implementation across your codebase. This approach gives engineering teams the flexibility to use their preferred frameworks and tools while benefiting from Webflow&#39;s streamlined deployment process and built-in performance optimization."
  }
}

{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Question",
  "name": "How does Webflow compare to traditional platforms for engineering teams?",
  "acceptedAnswer": {
    "@type": "Answer",
    "text": "Webflow stands apart from traditional CMS platforms and website builders by providing engineering teams with clean, semantic code output and professional-grade development capabilities without the limitations of template-based systems. Unlike platforms that restrict customization or require extensive plugin management, Webflow offers the flexibility of custom development with the efficiency of visual tools, enabling teams to build exactly what they envision without compromise. For engineering teams, Webflow combines the content management capabilities of enterprise platforms with the development flexibility typically reserved for custom-coded solutions. This unique approach allows developers to maintain full control over their codebase while accelerating delivery timelines, making it an ideal solution for teams that need both creative freedom and technical precision in their web development projects."
  }
}
